\pard\f0\fs20 So basically we can imprint maps on any kind of stone.\par
\pard\f0\fs20 We use this immersion printing, hydrographic printing to get it on.\par
\pard\f0\fs20 It's pigment based and then there's a clear coat.\par
\pard\f0\fs20 So they're very durable.\par
\pard\f0\fs20 We've created a composer, a browser based composer interface which allows you to work with a bunch of map styles.\par
\pard\f0\fs20 I could show you that if you guys want.\par
\pard\f0\fs20 And basically you compose the stone and then you can to send off the order.\par
\pard\f0\fs20 We embed a NTAG 424 DNA, which is a product authenticating chip.\par
\pard\f0\fs20 So and we also put in these three words, so if you don't have a NFC reader on your phone, you can do it manually.\par
\pard\f0\fs20 And we see this as the opportunity is to create a conversational AI agent whom we did a little prototype.\par
