\pard\f0\fs20 So.\par
\pard\par\f1\fs22\b\cf0 Hanif Janmohamed:\b0\par
\pard\f0\fs20 You can get into a relational conversation with the stone and the stone becomes what we call a planetary emissary.\par
\pard\f0\fs20 There's a couple of ways to create a network.\par
\pard\f0\fs20 One is through the sharing of a stone, so that connects people.\par
\pard\f0\fs20 That's a more serendipitous network.\par
\pard\f0\fs20 We call it an affinity network.\par
\pard\f0\fs20 And the second kind is two stones connecting on one phone or two devices in one location.\par
\pard\f0\fs20 So you can create kind of expanding networks of your stone or pairing through pairing.\par
\pard\f0\fs20 So what we see is a kind of opportunity between the physical and virtual engagement to create an interconnected distributed intelligence with the AI to really get us more grounded into an understanding of the shared space that we have, the planet.\par
\pard\f0\fs20 So a more eco conscious engagement with the virtual world.\par
\pard\f0\fs20 So yeah, our vision is a novel, intentional networks of decentralized eco conscious change makers.\par
\pard\f0\fs20 One of the things we did in our research papers was look at said network formation.\par
\pard\f0\fs20 And one of the things that was kind of interesting was the idea of weak ties, which is a term created by one of the researchers.\par
\pard\f0\fs20 And it relates to, you know, how, to how innovation moves in and out of siloed networks.\par
\pard\f0\fs20 And so we felt this was one kind of good way for us to look at network formation.\par
\pard\f0\fs20 So that's a key piece for us and we've applied to create a BC for funding for pilots.\par
\pard\f0\fs20 And what we see with that is 144 stones distributed in Vancouver or B.C.\par
\pard\f0\fs20 circulating in kind of diverse communities.\par
\pard\f0\fs20 And that's our learning experience.\par
\pard\f0\fs20 And the ask here is to try to put together a collective jam for building this infrastructure structure for the circulation of the maps for the stones.\par
\pard\f0\fs20 There's an AI tech stack to build a platform and a scalable framework for the emergent AI.\par
\pard\f0\fs20 We did some proof of concepts of.\par
